 <H1>Find the age of the youngest sailor with age    18, for each rating with at least 2 such sailors</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Only S.rating and S.age are mentioned in the SELECT, GROUP BY or HAVING clauses; other attributes `unnecessary’.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>2nd column of result is unnamed.  (Use AS to name it.)</H2>
</UL></P>
<P><UL>
SELECT  S.rating,  MIN (S.age)
<BR></UL><UL>
FROM  Sailors S
</UL><UL>
WHERE  S.age &#062= 18
</UL><UL>
GROUP BY  S.rating
</UL><UL>
HAVING  COUNT (*) &#062 1</UL></P>
